88"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-HuygensFryWSJ-12"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-HuygensFryWSJ_12-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation news">Jason Fry (January 23, 2006). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB113751632447848689">"Message in a Bottle"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Wall_Street_Journal" title="The Wall Street Journal">The Wall Street Journal</a></i>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJon+Lomberg&amp;rft.atitle=Message+in+a+Bottle&amp;rft.au=Jason+Fry&amp;rft.date=2006-01-23&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Wall+Street+Journal&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2FSB113751632447848689&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-ImageCoverContact-13"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-ImageCoverContact_13-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.biblio.com/details.php?dcx=43117558&amp;aid=frg">Description of first edition first printing</a><sup class="noprint Inline-Template"><span style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Link_rot" title="Wikipedia:Link rot"><span title="&#160;Dead link since April 2017">permanent dead link</span></a></i>]</span></sup> of <i><a href="/wiki/Contact_(novel)" title="Contact (novel)">Contact</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/Carl_Sagan" title="Carl Sagan">Carl Sagan</a>. <a href="/wiki/London" title="London">London</a>: <a href="/wiki/Hutchinson_(publisher)" title="Hutchinson (publisher)">Century Hutchinson</a>, 1986. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-7126-9503-6" title="Special:BookSources/0-7126-9503-6">0-7126-9503-6</a>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Sailing_Ship_Logo-14"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Sailing_Ship_Logo_14-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Jon Lomberg\'s <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://38.media.tumblr.com/fe7964aa4b3c6e1ee44d2f05ce745937/tumblr_inline_mpulu5T2n31qz4rgp.gif">Original Sailing Ship Logo</a> for the <a href="/wiki/Planetary_Society" class="mw-redirect" title="Planetary Society">Planetary Society</a>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-MilkyWayPortraitAbstract-15"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-MilkyWayPortraitAbstract_15-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-MilkyWayPortraitAbstract_15-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Goldstein, J. J.; Bicay, M.; Gorchev, R.; Lomberg, J.; Blitz, L.; Neal, V. <a href="/wiki/Abstract_(summary)" title="Abstract (summary)">Abstract</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://articles.adsabs.harvard.edu//full/1994BAAS...26.1549./0001550.000.html">A Portrait of the Milky Way: The Jon Lomberg Painting. Art and Science Working Together</a>. <a href="/wiki/American_Astronomical_Society" title="American Astronomical Society">American Astronomical Society</a>, <a href="/wiki/Division_for_Planetary_Sciences" title="Division for Planetary Sciences">DPS</a> Meeting #26, <i>Bulletin of the American Astronomical Society,</i> Vol. 26, p. 1550. December 1994.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-MilkyWayPortraitStarDate-16"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-MilkyWayPortraitStarDate_16-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web">David S. F. Portree. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://members.aol.com/dsfportree/sdate.htm">"New View of the Galaxy (December 2, 1994)"</a>. <i>Scripts of the <a href="/wiki/Broadcast_syndication#Radio_syndication" title="Broadcast syndication">syndicated radio</a> series</i> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://stardate.org/radio/">StarDate</a> <i>produced by the <a href="/wiki/McDonald_Observatory" title="McDonald Observatory">McDonald Observatory</a></i>. <q>Artist John Lomberg and astrophysicist Jeff Goldstein spent a year plotting the positions of <a href="/wiki/Nebula" title="Nebula">nebulae</a> and <a href="/wiki/Star_cluster" title="Star cluster">star clusters</a> we can see in the night sky. They also drew upon the latest research about the galaxy\'s structure. They used <a href="/wiki/Radio_astronomy" title="Radio astronomy">radio observations</a> to plot the broad sweep of its <a href="/wiki/Spiral_galaxy#Spiral_arms" title="Spiral galaxy">spiral arms</a>, for example. Lomberg then set up a six-foot-by-eight-foot canvas in a hut on the <a href="/wiki/Hawaii_(island)" title="Hawaii (island)">island of Hawaii</a>. He painted with <a href="/wiki/Airbrush" title="Airbrush">airbrush</a> and <a href="/wiki/Acrylic_paint" title="Acrylic paint">acrylics</a>. At night he covered the forming galaxy to keep the <a href="/wiki/Gecko" title="Gecko">geckos</a> away\xe2\x80\xa6</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJon+Lomberg&amp;rft.atitle=New+View+of+the+Galaxy+%28December+2%2C+1994%29&amp;rft.au=David+S.+F.+Portree&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Scripts+of+the+syndicated+radio+series+%27%27%5Bhttp%3A%2F%2Fstardate.org%2Fradio%2F+StarDate%5D%27%27+produced+by+the+McDonald+Observatory&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fmembers.aol.com%2Fdsfportree%2Fsdate.htm&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> <span style="font-size:100%" class="error citation-comment">External link in <code style="color:inherit; border:inherit; padding:inherit;">|work=</code> (<a href="/wiki/Help:CS1_errors#param_has_ext_link" title="Help:CS1 errors">help</a>)</span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-MilkyWayPortraitStellarium-17"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-MilkyWayPortraitStellarium_17-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web">Stellarium. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.stellarium.com/html/smithsonian.html">"Smithsonian National Air and Space Museum, 1992 - 2002"</a>. <q>[Image caption.] Installation of the map in 1992. Note the cutout in the light baffle wall on the right. It held a backlit Milky Way portrait by Emmy Award winning space artist Jon Lomberg. The portrait faced outward and served as a Stellarium introduction. Research by the museum\'s astrophysics department gave the renowned artist the basis for the most accurate portrait possible. It also gave the first evidence that our galaxy is a <a href="/wiki/Barred_spiral_galaxy" title="Barred spiral galaxy">barred spiral</a>.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJon+Lomberg&amp;rft.au=Stellarium&amp;rft.btitle=Smithsonian+National+Air+and+Space+Museum%2C+1992+-+2002&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.stellarium.com%2Fhtml%2Fsmithsonian.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-MilkyWayPortraitGarden-18"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-MilkyWayPortraitGarden_18-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.galaxygarden.net/mapping.html">"Mapping The Milky Way in Flowers"</a>. <i>Paleaku Astronomy Center Galaxy Garden, detailed description with photographs and explanatory diagrams</i>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJon+Lomberg&amp;rft.atitle=Mapping+The+Milky+Way+in+Flowers&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Paleaku+Astronomy+Center+Galaxy+Garden%2C+detailed+description+with+photographs+and+explanatory+diagrams&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.galaxygarden.net%2Fmapping.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-MarsDialScienceDaily-19"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-MarsDialScienceDaily_19-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-MarsDialScienceDaily_19-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/1999/04/990422055433.htm">"Martian Sundial Designed For 2001 Space Mission Is Unveiled By Bill Nye "The Science Guy<span style="padding-right:0.2em;">"</span>"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Science_Daily" title="Science Daily">Science Daily</a></i>. April 22, 1999.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJon+Lomberg&amp;rft.atitle=Martian+Sundial+Designed+For+2001+Space+Mission+Is+Unveiled+By+Bill+Nye+%22The+Science+Guy%22&amp;rft.date=1999-04-22&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Science+Daily&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedaily.com%2Freleases%2F1999%2F04%2F990422055433.htm&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-MarsDialStarBulletin-20"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-MarsDialStarBulletin_20-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web">Susan Essoyan (January 3, 2004). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://starbulletin.com/2004/01/03/news/story6.html">"Isle artist adds local touch to Mars craft"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Honolulu_Star-Bulletin" title="Honolulu Star-Bulletin">Honolulu Star-Bulletin</a></i>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJon+Lomberg&amp;rft.atitle=Isle+artist+adds+local+touch+to+Mars+craft&amp;rft.au=Susan+Essoyan&amp;rft.date=2004-01-03&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle